'''Ioan''' (or '''Ion''') '''Bogolea''' (born 1940, died ?<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.prosport.ro/sport-life/special/romania-sarbatoreste-50-de-ani-de-glorie-in-handbal-cand-eram-regii-lumii-8043950|title=România sărbătoreşte 50 de ani de glorie în handbal! Când eram regii lumii|language=Romanian|accessdate=April 27, 2014}}</ref>) was a Romanian [[handball]] player, who was double world champion. He was a goalkeeper.

After playing for Flamura Roșie [[Sighișoara]],<ref name="FRH">{{cite web|url=http://www.frh.ro/frh/pdf/istoria_jocului/Reconstructie-Consolidare-Glorie%201946-1962.pdf|title=RECONSTRUCŢIE – CONSOLIDARE – GLORIE PRIMELE MEDALII.|language=Romanian|accessdate=April 27, 2014}}</ref> he transferred to [[CS Dinamo Bucureşti (men's handball)|Dinamo Bucharest]].

He won the world championships twice with the Romanian team, in [[1961 World Men's Handball Championship|1961 in Germany]] and [[1964 World Men's Handball Championship|in 1964 in Czekoslovakia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bestsports.com.br/db/atlpag.php?atl=15049&lang=2|accessdate=April 27, 2014|title=Profile - Ioan BOGOLEA}}</ref>

He won a bronze medal in the World University Championship in [[Lund]], Sweden in 1963.<ref name="FRH"/>

As a member of Dinamo Bucharest he won, among others, the national championship and the [[EHF Champions League]].<ref name="FRH"/>

==Awards==
*Master of Sport, 1961<ref name="FRH2">{{cite web|url=http://www.frh.ro/ANEXA%202%20NUM2.htm|title=80 de ani de handbal in Romania|language=Romanian|accessdate=May 19, 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120404214835/http://www.frh.ro/ANEXA%202%20NUM2.htm|archivedate=April 4, 2012|df=}}</ref>
*Honored Master of Sport, 1964<ref name="FRH2"/>

